data.text: building ♦ property ♦ premises ♦ complex ♦ structure ♦ block ♦ edifice

data.chText: 以上各词均指建筑物、房屋、楼房。
data.enText: These are all words for a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls.

data.chText: 指建筑物、房屋、楼房
data.enText: a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls

data.chText: 指房屋及院落、庄园、房地产：
data.enText: a building or buildings and the surrounding land; land and buildings

data.chText: 我们有一买主想看看这房产。
data.enText: We have a buyer who would like to view the property.

data.chText: 房地产的价格大幅上升了。
data.enText: The price of property has risen enormously.

data.chText: 谈及买卖房屋或房地产时常用该词。
data.enText: This word is often used when talking about buying/selling houses or other buildings and land.

data.chText: 指企业拥有或使用的建筑及附属场地、营业场所：
data.enText: [pl.] the building or buildings and surrounding land that a business owns or uses

data.chText: 这家公司正在寻找更大的营业场所。
data.enText: The company is looking for larger premises.

data.chText: 指类型相似的建筑群：
data.enText: a group of buildings of a similar type together in one place

data.chText: 休闲活动中心

data.enText: a thing that is made of several parts, especially a building

data.chText: 这个码头是木结构建筑。
data.enText: The pier is a wooden structure.

data.chText: 指公寓、办公大楼或学校、医院等作特定用途的大楼：
data.enText: ( BrE ) a tall building that contains flats or offices; a building that forms part of a school, hospital, etc. and is used for a particular purpose

data.chText: 公寓大楼
这所学校的理科大楼

data.text: structure ♦ framework ♦ composition ♦ construction ♦ fabric ♦ make-up

data.chText: 以上各词均指事物各个不同部分的组合、构造。
data.enText: These are all words for the way the different parts of sth combine together or the way that sth has been made.

data.chText: 指结构、构造：
data.enText: the way in which the parts of sth are connected together or arranged; a particular arrangement of parts

data.chText: 建筑物／人体结构
data.enText: the structure of the building/human body

data.chText: 社会的社会结构
一种语言的语法结构
data.enText: the grammatical structures of a language

data.chText: 工资结构
指构成某个体系或社会基础的信仰、观点、准则：
data.enText: a set of beliefs, ideas or rules that forms the basis of a system or society

data.chText: 报告提供了进一步研究的原则。
data.enText: The report provides a framework for further research.

data.chText: 指不同部分或人的构成、组合方式：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) the different parts or people that combine to form sth; the way in which they combine

data.chText: 劳动力组合最近的变化
data.enText: recent changes in the composition of the workforce

data.chText: 指建造或构造：
data.enText: the way that sth has been built or made

data.chText: 钢结构船
指社会、机构等的基本结构：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) the basic structure of a society or an organization that enables it to function successfully

data.chText: 这是威胁社会基本结构的趋势。
data.enText: This is a trend which threatens the very fabric of society .

data.chText: 指不同人或事物的构成、构成方式：
data.enText: the different people or things that combine to form sth; the way in which they combine

data.chText: 动植物基因的构成
data.enText: the genetic make-up of plants and animals

data.chText: 用composition还是make-up？
上述两词的主要区别在于使用场合的正式程度。composition较常用于科技语境，make-up则较常用于口语和新闻报道中。make-up亦指人的性格、气质。
data.enText: The main difference between these words is the level of formality. Composition is more often used in scientific and technical contexts; make-up is more often used in speech and journalism. Make-up also means the different qualities that combine to form sb's character.

ex.chText: 这座教堂是中世纪建筑风格的典型实例。
ex.enText: This church is a classic example of medieval architecture.

ex.chText: 最终她获得了建筑学的学位证书。

ex.chText: 公众强烈反对修建新机场。

ex.chText: 所有这些图片都取材于现代建筑。
ex.enText: All these pictures are about modern construction.

synonyms.bx: 指施工过程，也可指建造物本身。

ex.enText: That stone structure dates back to the Ming Dynasty.

synonyms.bx: 指拥有多个部分的大型建筑物。

tr: a complex entity constructed of many parts
example: the structure consisted of a series of arches
she wore her hair in an amazing construction of whirls and ribbons

tr: the manner of construction of something and the arrangement of its parts
example: artists must study the structure of the human body
the structure of the benzene molecule

tr: a particular complex anatomical part of a living thing
the complex composition of knowledge as elements and their combinations
the people in a society considered as a system organized by a characteristic pattern of relationships
example: the social organization of England and America is very different
sociologists have studied the changing structure of the family
I need to structure my days

value.def: The structure of something is the way in which it is made, built, or organized.

example.ex: The typical family structure of Freud's patients involved two parents and two children...
example.tran: 弗洛伊德的病人的典型家庭结构是父母二人和两个孩子。

example.ex: The chemical structure of this particular molecule is very unusual.
example.tran: 这个特殊分子的化学结构很不寻常。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: A structure is something that consists of parts connected together in an ordered way.

example.ex: The feet are highly specialised structures made up of 26 small delicate bones.
example.tran: 脚的结构非常特殊，由 26 块细小的骨头组成。

value.def: A structure is something that has been built.

example.ex: About half of those funds has gone to repair public roads, structures and bridges...
example.tran: 那些基金中大约有一半已被用来维修公路、公共建筑物和桥梁。

example.ex: The house was a handsome four-story brick structure.
example.tran: 这所房子是一幢造型美观的四层砖砌建筑物。

value.def: If you structure something, you arrange it in a careful, organized pattern or system.

example.ex: By structuring the course this way, we're forced to produce something the companies think is valuable.
example.tran: 这样制定发展规划后，我们不得不生产各公司认为有价值的东西。

value.tran: 系统安排;精心组织;使形成体系

example.ex: We have introduced a more structured training programme.
example.tran: 我们已经推出了一门更系统的培训课程。
